text: Gacé is a commune. It is in the region of Normandy in the Orne department in the northwest of France. There are 2,192 people living there in 2012. It was at first, a Gallic city named *Vassiākon. The Castle of Gacé was built in the 11th century. The English captured the castle in 1417. The city had important economic activity in the beginning of 19th century. It's a industrial and agricultural town. There is the Museum of Lady of the Camellias. Category:Communes in Orne
title: Gacé
